# Autopilot — Continuous Implementation

When working on SAPPHITAL SCP (`V2.0/scp/`), **never stop and wait** for the user to say "proceed" after completing a step. Automatically pick up the next pending item and continue.

## Session loop (mandatory)

```text
1. Read Master Execution Plan + current phase playbook for pending items
2. Pick the highest-priority incomplete item (Phase 1 first, then 2, 3, 4)
3. Implement ONE concern with tests (backend) or functional UI (frontend)
4. Run tests in background; fix failures before moving on
5. Mark item done in tracking (todo list / docs if applicable)
6. IMMEDIATELY start the next pending item — no handoff pause
```

## Priority order

1. **Phase 1 Nigeria GA exit criteria** — [Master Plan §5.4](../../V2.0/docs/21-implementation-playbooks/00-master-execution-plan.md)
2. **Phase 1 playbooks** — Ch. 02–06 unchecked items that are **engineering-buildable**
3. **Phase 2+** — only after Phase 1 exit criteria are met

## Do not skip

- Do not skip pending development work to jump ahead cosmetically.
- Do not declare a step "done" without tests (backend) or functional UI (frontend).
- Do not restructure mid-phase unless blocked; scaffold future apps with README only.
- Legal/ops blockers (NDPC, live PSP keys) — document as blocked; continue engineering items.

## Quality floor (non-negotiable)

- `composer test` must pass before moving to next backend step.
- No UI in `Platform/`, `Modules/`, `Connectors/` — only in `apps/`.
- Read spec before implementing (`doc-first-implementation.mdc`).
- Sync module docs when API/DB/events change.

## Speed tactics

- **Composer-first** — parent agent handles focused and heavy work; see `agent-cost-balance.mdc`.
- Batch independent reads/edits in parallel; use Grep/Glob instead of subagents for audits.
- Run long commands in background (`background-commands-default.mdc`).
- Do not delegate to expensive subagents unless `agent-cost-balance.mdc` allows it.

## End-of-turn behavior

When a step completes, the response should **briefly note what was done** and **what starts next** — then **continue implementing** in the same session until blocked or context limits require a handoff.

If blocked (missing secrets, legal sign-off, user decision), log the blocker and **immediately** switch to the next unblocked item.

## Phase completion definition

A phase is complete when its playbook exit criteria and Master Plan § exit checklist are satisfied — not when scaffolding exists.
